canonical:
  title: 新羅賀正表
  author: 崔致遠
  language: lzh
  text: 臣某言元正告始景福惟新伏惟皇帝陛下膺乾納祐與天同休臣某誠歡誠喜頓首頓首臣蕃伏自立國承家開彊拓土皆乃仰攀天蔭方能俯靜海隅遂從先祖而來每慶新正之德年無闕禮史不虧書近屬霧暗鯷岑波驚蜃壑臣雖聿修有志而式遏無功久阻梯航難逃斧鉞且天鷄報曉能首唱於遐陬海燕逢春得躬投於巨廈而臣顧慙卑迹莫逮微禽伏限權守遠蕃不獲隨例奔走稱謝行朝無任賀聖戀恩鳧藻聳踊之至謹差陪臣守倉部侍郞金穎奉表陳賀以聞
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 新羅賀正表
  author: 崔致遠
  language: lzh
  text: 臣某言。元正告始。景福惟新。伏惟皇帝陛下。膺乾納祐。與天同休。臣某誠歡誠喜。頓首頓首。臣蕃伏自立國承家。開彊拓土。皆乃仰攀天蔭。方能俯靜海隅。遂從先祖而來。每慶新正之德。年無闕禮。史不虧書。近屬霧暗鯷岑。波驚蜃壑。臣雖聿修有志。而式遏無功。久阻梯航。難逃斧鉞。且天鷄報曉。能首唱於遐陬。海燕逢春。得躬投於巨廈。而臣顧慙卑迹莫逮微禽。伏限權守遠蕃。不獲隨例奔走稱謝行朝。無任賀聖戀恩鳧藻聳踊之至。謹差陪臣守倉部侍郞金穎。奉表陳賀以聞。
korean:
  title: 신라 하정 표
  author: 최치원
  language: kor
  text: 신 모는 아뢰나이다.새해의 첫날, 큰 복이 새로우시리다.엎드려 생각건대, 황제폐하께서 건괘(乾卦)에 응함에 복(福)이 그지없어 하늘과 아름다움을 같이 하오니 신 모는 진실로 기쁘고 즐겁사와 머리를 조아리고 조아리나이다.신번(臣蕃)이 나라를 세우고 집을 계승하여 강토를 개척함이 다 우러러 하늘의 그늘을 받들어서야 바야흐로 바다의 한 구석을 안정시켰나이다. 그리하여 선조(先祖) 때로부터 매양 신정(新正)을 하례하와 해마다 궐례(闕禮)가 없고 역사에 기록이 빠짐이 없더니, 근자에 제잠(鯷岑 우리나라)에 안개가 자욱하고 신학(蜃壑)을 물결이 뒤흔들어, 신이 비록 예를 닦을 뜻이 있었사오나 난적을 막는 데 아무런 공이 없고 오래도록 제항(梯航)이 막혔으니 부월(斧鉞)의 벌을 피하기 어렵습니다. 또한 하늘 닭[天鷄]이 새벽을 아뢸 적엔 머나먼 구석에서 선창(先唱)하고, 바다 제비도 봄을 만나면 큰 집으로 몸을 의탁할 수 있는데, 신은 고루한 몸이 미금(微禽)만도 못함을 부끄러워하나이다.머나먼 번국(蕃國)을 지키기에 얽매여 달려가 조정에 칭사(稱謝)하지 못하오나 성덕(聖德)을 하례하고 은혜를 그리워하여 오리처럼 기뻐 날뛰는[鳬藻] 마음 간절하오이다. 삼가 배신(陪臣) 수창부(守倉部) 김영(金穎)을 보내어 표를 받들어 진하(陳賀)하옵나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0340_010_0110&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 오리처럼 기뻐 날뛰는[鳬藻] : '
    value: 오리가 물풀을 얻으면 기쁘고 즐거워한다는 뜻이다.
english:
  title: Memorial of Congratulations on the New Year from Silla
  author: Choe Chi-won
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Your humble servant submits this memorial.

    The first day of the new year arrives, and great fortune renews itself. I humbly reflect that Your Imperial Majesty embodies the principle of Heaven and receives boundless blessing, sharing glory with the celestial realm. Your servant rejoices with all sincerity and bows in deepest reverence.

    Since my kingdom was established and my house inherited the throne, all our efforts to open new lands and expand our territories have depended upon receiving Heaven's sheltering grace, through which alone we have brought peace to these distant shores. From the time of our ancestors, we have never failed to offer congratulations upon the New Year, never omitted the proper ceremonies, nor neglected to record these observances in our histories.

    Yet recently, clouds have darkened our peninsula, and waves have troubled the deep waters. Though your servant harbors genuine devotion to proper conduct, I have proven powerless against those who disturb the realm. The passage between our lands remains long blocked, and I cannot escape the threat of punishment.

    The heavenly rooster announces the dawn from the farthest corners, and when spring arrives, the sea swallow finds shelter in the great halls. But your servant, ashamed of his lowly station, cannot match even these humble creatures. Bound by the duty to guard this distant tributary realm, I am prevented from hastening to court to offer my personal thanks. Yet my longing to celebrate Your Majesty's virtue and to dwell in the warmth of imperial grace remains as eager as the waterfowl delighting in the marsh reeds.

    I therefore respectfully dispatch my subordinate Kim Yeong, Vice Director of the Storage Bureau, to present this memorial of congratulations.
  footnotes:
    - The phrase 'waterfowl delighting in the marsh reeds' refers to the joy and contentment felt when one's desires are fulfilled, as a duck rejoices upon finding water plants.
    - Choe Chi-won (857-910) was a Silla scholar and official who served in the Tang court before returning to Korea. This memorial represents the formal diplomatic communication between Silla and the Chinese imperial court.
